# Force LF line endings for all text files, in the working tree on every OS.
#
# Without this, GitHub's Windows CI runner (git core.autocrlf=true by default)
# checks our LF-stored files out as CRLF, and `zig fmt --check` — which requires
# LF — then fails on every file. Pinning eol=lf keeps the Windows checkout LF so
# the format gate (and clang-format, once C/C++ lands) passes cross-platform.
* text=auto eol=lf
